    • fromRunLengthEncoded

      public static <ELEMENT_TYPE> Hexahedron<ELEMENT_TYPE> fromRunLengthEncoded​(@NotNull @NotNull Point dimensions, @NotNull @NotNull String runLength, @NotNull @NotNull String termSeparator, @NotNull @NotNull String countSeparator, @NotNull @NotNull Function<String,​ELEMENT_TYPE> mappingFunction)
      Static method factory from RLE string.
      Type Parameters:
      ELEMENT_TYPE - generic type for elements.
      Parameters:
      dimensions - dimensions of the hexahedron to build.
      runLength - string to convert from RLE string to a hexahedron.
      termSeparator - string used as a separator between different terms (ex: ';' in 3:type;1:other).
      countSeparator - string used a a separator between the number of occurrences and the block type.
      mappingFunction - function that take the token from the RLE and returns the corresponding value to put in the hexahedron.
      Returns:
      the build Hexahedron.
